  "body": "Hi fellows!\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\nAfter months of running nethermind node it stuck a few blocks after Gray Glacier fork (client version 1.13.0). \r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/33096727/176993475-d475e4d6-4f68-4277-a188-8fa7962d3589.png)\r\n\r\nI upgraded client to 1.13.4, after unsuccessful restart attempts I quit, disposed the db and synced again. No success, I again and again face difficulty discrepancies right after pivot block. \r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/33096727/176993497-80d419bf-e083-4aae-8407-9025a00db977.png)\r\n\r\nI tried multiple different pivots/setups, still the same result.\r\nInitial sync setup:\r\n```  \r\n\"Sync\": {\r\n    \"FastSync\": true,\r\n    \"PivotNumber\": 15057100,\r\n    \"PivotHash\": \"0x3681d30f14489ea2cb9caf891e8074b0e108c8e5ff10ddd37db5af8541b1a306\",\r\n    \"PivotTotalDifficulty\": \"53010419136510774987329\",\r\n    \"FastBlocks\": true,\r\n    \"DownloadBodiesInFastSync\": false,\r\n    \"DownloadReceiptsInFastSync\": false,\r\n  },\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Desktop (please complete the following information):**\r\n - OS: ubuntu\r\n - Version: 1.13.4-0-3e5972c24-20220701/X64-Linux/6.0.6\r\n - logs: [mainnet.log](https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/files/9032677/mainnet.log)\r\n\r\nPlease take a look.\r\nThanks.",
